00:04:39.718 --> 00:04:41.284
which actually doesn't
change the equation.

00:04:41.284 --> 00:04:43.105
This actually is going to be--

00:04:43.105 --> 00:04:44.834
It changes it the way it looks,

00:04:44.834 --> 00:04:47.951
but it actually represents the same line.

00:04:47.951 --> 00:04:51.232
So this is definitely
still an equivalent system.

00:04:51.232 --> 00:04:52.851
These are still the same constraints.

00:04:52.851 --> 00:04:54.718
You're going to have the same solution.

00:04:54.718 --> 00:04:56.118
Whenever you're dealing with systems,

00:04:56.118 --> 00:04:58.818
you're not going to change
the solution of the system

00:04:58.818 --> 00:05:02.885
as long as you either multiply
both sides of an equation by

00:05:02.885 --> 00:05:05.651
a scaler, or you are adding
and subtracting the equations.

00:05:05.651 --> 00:05:07.184
When I say add or subtract the equations,

00:05:07.184 --> 00:05:09.085
you're adding the left-hand
side to the left-hand side,

00:05:09.085 --> 00:05:10.752
adding the right-hand side
to the right-hand side

00:05:10.752 --> 00:05:14.285
like we had here, or subtracting
the one from the other

00:05:14.285 --> 00:05:16.651
on the left-hand side and
if we subtract the bottom

00:05:16.651 --> 00:05:17.718
from the top on the left-hand

00:05:17.718 --> 00:05:19.751
and we subtract the bottom
from the top on the right-hand,

00:05:19.751 --> 00:05:21.785
it's not going to change our solution.

00:05:21.785 --> 00:05:25.417
So both of them obtained a
system that is equivalent,

00:05:25.417 --> 00:05:27.385
meaning that it has the same solution

00:05:27.385 --> 00:05:30.189
as the teacher's system.

